-- Kings Defeat Coyotes in Overtime to Advance to Stanley Cup Final
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-05-23T04:44:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/kings-defeat-coyotes-in-overtime-to-advance-to-stanley-cup-final.html
Dustin Penner scored in overtime and
the Los Angeles Kings advanced to the Stanley Cup Final, where
they will face the  New York Rangers  or the New Jersey Devils.  The Kings won the Western Conference finals four games to
one and set an NHL record with their eighth straight road
victory this postseason.  Anze Kopitar, Drew Doughty and Mike Richards also scored
for the Kings at the Jobing.com Arena in Glendale, Arizona.
Taylor Pyatt, Marc-Antoine Pouliot and Keith Yandle scored for
the Coyotes.  The Rangers and Devils are tied 2-2 in the Eastern
Conference finals, with Game 5 set for tonight at  New York â€™s
